 very important that any hypermedia link only provide such an attribute as =
a =93hint=94.

Yes.

In addition, I&#39;d recommend not to make use of type att=
ributes because they lead to unintended coupling between representations (o=
r the code that produces these representations) and the set of used media t=
ypes. Any time you remove or add support for a certain media type, you need=
 to check and update all the code that produces corresponding &#39;type&#39; attrib=
utes. That&#39;s likely to be a maintenance nightmare.







